{"word":"γνωστός","slug":"γνωστός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>γνωστός, ή, όν</el></b> [<el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:γινώσκω\">γινώσκω</a></el>; by-form of the older <el>γνωτός</el> ‘perceived, understood’, also ‘known’]<b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>1.</pp> <i>known,</i></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ freq.\">freq.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ dat.\">dat.</a> <b><i>known to</i><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of interpersonal relationship, as noun = <i>acquaintance,</i> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ abs.\">abs.</a> <b><a href='B:490 2:44'>Lk 2:44</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ dat.\">dat.</a> <b><a href='B:490 23:49'>23:49</a>;</b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ gen.\">gen.</a> <b><a href='B:500 18:16'>J 18:16</a>;</b> as <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pred.\">pred.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ w.\">w.</a> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ dat.\">dat.</a> in same sense <b><a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ vs.\">vs.</a> 15.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of things <b><a href='B:510 1:19'>Ac 1:19</a></b> and <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ oft.\">oft.</a> in Ac. <b><p class=\"pp1\"/>—<pp>2.</pp></b> ‘that which can be known’, <el>τὸ γνωστὸν τοῦ ϑεοῦ</el> <i>what may be known about God</i> <b><a href='B:520 1:19'>Ro 1:19</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:γνώστης\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:γογγύζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}